The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Cognizant earnings up 11%
                                                                                                               Cognizant earnings up 11%
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, May 5: Cognizant Technology Solutions has reported an 11 per cent increase in net income at $113.13 million for the first quarter ended March 31, 2009, against $101.87 million in the year-ago period.         
	The company, which has a prominent presence in India, also issued its 2009 revenue outlook of at least $3.1 billion, up 10 per cent over the 2008 figure.         
	During the period under review, Cognizant posted a 16 per cent rise in revenue to $745.9 million from $643.1 million a year ago.        
	The company expects earnings of 37 cents per share on a revenue of at least $760 million in the second quarter.         
	We are pleased with our performance during the first quarter, which exceeded our revenue guidance and demonstrated Cognizants continued ability to outperform the industry, CEO and president, Francisco DSouza, said.        
	We remain confident of achieving our full-year guidance of at least 10 per cent revenue growth, he said.         
	Cognizant ended the first quarter with nearly $969 million in cash, which it intends to use in short- and long-term investments. Cognizants chief financial and operating officer Gordon Coburn said the company repurchased shares of over $12 million during the first quarter.                                                                                                                                                                  
